  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What does "DE Rantau" mean?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          "Rantau" means "migration" or "wandering" in Malay—a nod to the nomadic lifestyle. DE stands for Digital Economy. The program is run by MDEC (Malaysia Digital Economy Corporation).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I work for Malaysian clients?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The DE Rantau is designed for remote workers serving clients outside Malaysia. Working primarily for Malaysian clients would require different work authorization.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is SafetyWing accepted?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, Malaysia is relatively flexible about insurance. SafetyWing and similar travel medical insurance are typically accepted for DE Rantau applications.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I bring my family?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Dependents (spouse and children) can apply for dependent passes at 500 MYR (~$109) each. They must be included in or applied alongside your main application.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">KL or Penang—which is better?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          KL is larger, more urban, with better nightlife and international amenities. Penang is smaller, cheaper, with better food and beaches, more relaxed vibe. Both have strong nomad communities.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Does DE Rantau lead to permanent residency?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. The DE Rantau is a professional pass, not a residency pathway. For permanent residency, you'd need to explore other programs like MM2H (Malaysia My Second Home).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

